The paper discusses a distributed, cooperative framework and method for Bayesian estimation and control in decentralized agent networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of belief propagation message passing and consensus for cooperative estimation, which are commonly used techniques in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of gradient ascent for cooperative control, which is a common optimization technique in Robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper mentions the use of probabilistic information in the form of sample representations of probability distributions, which is a common topic in Information Theory (cs.IT).
